---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import concept from '../../../../assets/concept.png';
---
<BaseLayout title="Marionette Documentation" lang="en" languageSwitcherPath="/marionette/ja/">
  <h1>Marionette Documentation</h1>
  <p class="lead">Tutorials, API reference, and component examples for Marionette.</p>
  <figure class="concept-figure">
    <img src={concept.src} width={concept.width} height={concept.height} alt="Marionette concept diagram" />
  </figure>

  <section class="top-section" aria-labelledby="docs-role-en">
    <h2 id="docs-role-en">What This Site Covers</h2>
    <p>
      The README stays focused on the value of Marionette. Use this documentation site for getting started, API details, and component usage.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="top-section" aria-labelledby="quick-start-en">
    <h2 id="quick-start-en">Quick Start</h2>
    <p>The fastest path to try Marionette in under three minutes.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Build your first app: <a href="/marionette/en/tutorial/">Tutorial</a></li>
      <li>Run the full demo: <code>go run ./cmd/marionette</code></li>
      <li>Run the minimal sample: <code>go run ./cmd/simple-sample</code></li>
      <li>Read the API reference: <a href="/marionette/en/api/">API Docs</a></li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="top-section" aria-labelledby="pathways-en">
    <h2 id="pathways-en">Navigate by Goal</h2>
    <div class="top-cards">
      <a class="top-card" href="/marionette/en/tutorial/"><h3>Tutorial</h3><p>Start: Create a project and reach Hello World step by step.</p></a>
      <a class="top-card" href="/marionette/en/components/"><h3>Components Gallery</h3><p>Try: Explore component visuals and structure.</p></a>
      <a class="top-card" href="/marionette/en/api/"><h3>API Docs</h3><p>Learn: Understand Page / Action / Context APIs.</p></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
